The paper discusses a framework for handling uncertain data in constraint programming, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The framework involves combining methodologies from different fields, such as reliable computation and constraint programming, which suggests that it may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions a case study in network diagnosis, which could fall under data mining (cs.DM) or software engineering (cs.SE).
